        "PESQPROJRESUMOINGVC": "A scientific community or a research group is more than a conglomeration of people. In this context, such academic organizations have their own structures that are constituted in the practices carried out and in the relationships between the subjects. In this way, the present umbrella-type project aims to analyze the constitution of the scientific community in social technologies and childhood from research groups, questioning its resonances for science and mathematics education. To this end, four steps are proposed: a) survey of research groups; b) cataloging the group's production themes; c) Perceptions of research group coordinators; d) propositions for Science and Mathematics Education. The analysis approach is based on qualitative and quantitative assumptions, using interviews, questionnaires and documents as data collection instruments. As a result, it is expected to map themes, intentions and elements of the constitution of research groups, as well as their potential for science and mathematics education.",
